  <h2>Avila, Cheval &amp; Villarosa: gated-community service</h2>
  <p>Gated Lutz communities (<strong>Avila, Cheval, Villarosa, Heritage Harbor</strong>) have specific access, noise, and HOA rules we navigate every week. We coordinate directly with gate security, bring the required insurance certificates, schedule installs outside noise-ordinance hours, and complete any required HOA condenser-placement approval forms. Most estate-grade systems we install here are 2-stage or variable-speed 17–21 SEER2 with dedicated humidity control — the comfort difference in a 5,000+ sq. ft. Avila home is substantial.</p>

  <h2>Lutz Lake Fern corridor &amp; unincorporated older Lutz</h2>
  <p>The Lutz Lake Fern, Livingston, Bearss, and US-41 corridors have a lot of 1950s–1980s single-family and hobby-farm homes with original ductwork in unconditioned attics. On these homes, replacing the condenser without addressing the ducts wastes money. Our proposal for this vintage always includes a duct inspection and honest advice on what's worth sealing, what's worth replacing, and what should just be left alone — you'd be surprised how often "just seal the takeoffs" fixes a comfort complaint more cheaply than a new condenser.</p>

  <h2>Calusa Trace, Sunlake &amp; Heritage Harbor: established community replacements</h2>
  <p>These 1990s–early-2000s communities are hitting the peak of their HVAC-replacement wave. Most original 10–13 SEER single-stage condensers are 18–22 years old and past economic repair. We handle these same-week: Manual-J load calc, three-tier written proposal, HOA approval form, permit submittal, day-of-install, and inspection coordination. Financing available through Synchrony for qualified Lutz homeowners.</p>

